![Example Image](xkaasay.png)

Just an attempt to rewrite xcow using python. Kaa is the python in the Jungle Book
and it also sounds a bit like xcow from xcowsay.

The snake (and the other animals) image is a freeware from Martin Berube and it was
taken from http://www.softicons.com/animal-icons/animal-icons-by-martin-berube/snake-icon

the default font comes from : http://openfontlibrary.org/en/:font/benveno

INSTALLATION
============
Requirements: Python 3, pygame, Pillow

Install dependencies:
    pip install -r requirements.txt

USAGE
=====
Run the xkaasay script:
    ./xkaasay -c snake -a say -t "Hello World!" -i blue

Options:
    -c, --character : Character name (snake, bat, donkey, etc.)
    -a, --action    : Action type (say, shout, think, dream)
    -t, --text      : Text to display
    -i, --ink       : Ink color (black, red, blue, green)
    -d, --dream     : Path to dream image (for dream action)

Controls:
    - Left click and drag to move the window
    - Right click or ESC to close
